2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:820:\"<p>If you&#8217;ve not yet tried out our sister company&#8217;s free &#8220;two factor&#8221; authentication plugin, available in the wordpress.org directory for everyone, then please do take a look. Since its recent release, it&#8217;s already gathered over 100 active users who are &#8230; <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com/two-factor-authentication-premium-version-now-available/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com/two-factor-authentication-premium-version-now-available/\">Two factor authentication &#8211; Premium version now available</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"udadmin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1399:\"<p>If you&#8217;ve not yet tried out our sister company&#8217;s <a title=\"Plugin of the week – two-factor authentication\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com/plugin-of-the-week-two-factor-authentication/\">free &#8220;two factor&#8221; authentication plugin</a>, available in the wordpress.org directory for everyone, then please do take a look. Since its recent release, it&#8217;s already gathered over 100 active users who are now protected against hackers guessing their passwords, using industry standard protocols (don&#8217;t use home-cooked ideas to set up your site&#8217;s security!).</p>\n\n<p>If you have tried it out, then you may be interested to know that a cheaply-priced premium version with more features is now available, <a title=\"Two Factor Authentication - Premium version\" href=\"https://www.simbahosting.co.uk/s3/product/two-factor-authentication/\">at this link</a>. It&#8217;s on a sale price at approximately 33% off for the next fortnight.</p>\n\n<p>David Anderson (founder, lead developer, UpdraftPlus)</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com/two-factor-authentication-premium-version-now-available/\">Two factor authentication &#8211; Premium version now available</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"http://updraftplus.com/two-factor-authentication-premium-version-now-available/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"http://updraftplus.com/two-factor-authentication-premium-version-now-available/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"UpdraftPlus 1.9.63 / 2.9.63\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/UpdraftPlus/~3/Iw36x6HxanA/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"http://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-1-9-63-2-9-63/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 03 Apr 2015 20:38:34 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"updates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"amazon s3\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"new release\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"http://updraftplus.com/?p=106761\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:690:\"<p>UpdraftPlus 1.9.63 (free) / 2.9.63 (paid) has just been released. It&#8217;s the same as 1.9.62 / 2.9.62, with only one tweak; we have reverted to bundling the previous selection of SSL certificates, because it appears that some Amazon S3 servers &#8230; <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-1-9-63-2-9-63/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-1-9-63-2-9-63/\">UpdraftPlus 1.9.63 / 2.9.63</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"udadmin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1187:\"<p>UpdraftPlus 1.9.63 (free) / 2.9.63 (paid) has just been released.</p>\n\n<p>It&#8217;s the same as 1.9.62 / 2.9.62, with only one tweak; we have reverted to bundling the previous selection of SSL certificates, because it appears that some Amazon S3 servers are still using weak 1024-bit encryption. The Firefox and Chrome web browsers stopped accepting these <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-1-9-26/\">over 6 months ago</a>, but it seems that Amazon still have some S3 servers that use them. (S3&#8217;s usually visited by automated tools, rather than web browsers &#8211; but, it&#8217;s a good benchmark of what&#8217;s considered up to modern standards).So, if your S3 backups were failing due to SSL validation errors, then you should update to this. Otherwise, updating will make no difference.</p>\n\n<p>David Anderson (founder, lead developer, UpdraftPlus)</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-1-9-63-2-9-63/\">UpdraftPlus 1.9.63 / 2.9.63</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-1-9-63-2-9-63/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:49:\"http://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-1-9-63-2-9-63/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"New plugins – what’s coming down the river?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/UpdraftPlus/~3/qPgsdYnWz0Y/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"http://updraftplus.com/new-plugins-whats-coming-down-the-river/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 03 Apr 2015 09:28:24 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"We recommend\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"http://updraftplus.com/?p=106312\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:742:\"<p>Last time I checked, the wordpress.org plugin repository claimed to have 37,022 plugins available. By the time you read this, there&#8217;ll be more. And, we&#8217;ll both be happy to remain ignorant forever of at least 99% of those. But what &#8230; <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com/new-plugins-whats-coming-down-the-river/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com/new-plugins-whats-coming-down-the-river/\">New plugins &#8211; what&#8217;s coming down the river?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"udadmin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3439:\"<p>Last time I checked, the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/\">wordpress.org plugin repositor</a>y claimed to have <strong>37,022 </strong>plugins available. By the time you read this, there&#8217;ll be more.</p>\n\n<p>And, we&#8217;ll both be happy to remain ignorant forever of at least 99% of those. But what about the other 1%? How to find the good ones, and the ones that scratch your itch?</p>\n\n<p>Well, I&#8217;ve been keeping up with &#8220;just released&#8221; new plugins, to see what looks like it has promise. Note: I&#8217;ve not installed or tested them all. This is a first impression, based on the areas I&#8217;m interested in. I&#8217;m not going to list 100 things just to fill space; these are the ones that caught my eye as worth a second look. Here we go&#8230;</p>\n\n<ol>\n    <li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/postcode-based-order-restriction/\">Postcode Based Order Restriction for WooCommerce</a>\nThis looks handy if you run a business that can only fulfil orders locally (e.g. a fast food restaurant). WooCommerce,  out of the box, allows you to restrict to particular countries &#8211; but that&#8217;s not enough for businesses of this sort. (If you do run a fast food restaurant, you might find <a href=\"https://www.simbahosting.co.uk/s3/product/woocommerce-opening-hours-delivery-times/\">this</a> and <a href=\"https://www.simbahosting.co.uk/s3/product/woocommerce-automatic-order-printing/\">this</a> very handy too).</li>\n    <li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/remove-wp-branding/\">Remove WP Branding</a>\nDo you want to white-label a WordPress install for your clients? This is a plugin to do that.</li>\n    <li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wpit-blog-stats/\">Wpit Blog Stats</a>\nPublish stats about readership and commenting activity on your blog. If you want activity logs, then <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-activity-log/\">there&#8217;s also this new one</a>.</li>\n    <li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/email-client/\">Email Client</a>\nA webmail client inside your WordPress install &#8211; what next? Still: I can see some people will like this: could be useful if you manage a lot else from inside there (e.g. your invoices (like with <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/smart-invoice-and-billing-management/\">this new one</a>), or support tickets, etc.).</li>\n    <li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/admin-custom-login/\">Custom Login Plugin</a>\nThat&#8217;s not the world&#8217;s snappiest name, but it&#8217;s something a lot of people want: an easy way to brand and re-design the WordPress login page, which is both a bit dated in its look, and advertises WordPress instead of advertising your site.\n\n&#8230; and, if you&#8217;ve not yet seen it, our new one for you:</li>\n    <li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/two-factor-authentication/\">Two Factor Authentication</a>\nSecure your WordPress site with industry-standard two-factor authentication.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>Hope you found something that interested you in there!</p>\n\n<p>David Anderson (founder, lead developer, UpdraftPlus)</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com/new-plugins-whats-coming-down-the-river/\">New plugins &#8211; what&#8217;s coming down the river?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68:\"http://updraftplus.com/new-plugins-whats-coming-down-the-river/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"http://updraftplus.com/new-plugins-whats-coming-down-the-river/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"WordPress 4.2 “shiny updates”\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/UpdraftPlus/~3/1v0BuXLy5nU/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"http://updraftplus.com/wordpress-4-2-shiny-updates/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 02 Apr 2015 14:28:13 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"updates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"automatic backups\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21:\"new wordpress release\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"http://updraftplus.com/?p=106289\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:721:\"<p>&#8220;WP Beginner&#8221; has a decent run-down of what&#8217;s coming in WordPress 4.2, here. In summary&#8230; Improved emoji support. I must be off the pace: I was still calling these &#8220;smileys&#8221;. Does it differ in different parts of the world? A &#8230; <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com/wordpress-4-2-shiny-updates/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com/wordpress-4-2-shiny-updates/\">WordPress 4.2 &#8220;shiny updates&#8221;</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"udadmin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4513:\"<p>&#8220;WP Beginner&#8221; has a decent run-down of what&#8217;s coming in WordPress 4.2, <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/news/whats-coming-in-wordpress-4-2-features-and-screenshots/\">here</a>. In summary&#8230;</p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>Improved emoji support. I must be off the pace: I was still calling these &#8220;smileys&#8221;. Does it differ in different parts of the world?</li>\n    <li>A theme switcher built into the dashboard&#8217;s &#8220;customizer&#8221;.</li>\n    <li>&#8220;Shiny plugin updates&#8221;.</li>\n    <li>&#8220;Press this&#8221; improvements.</li>\n    <li>Under the hood things</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Feeling under-whelmed? Me too!\nOn the other hand&#8230; I much prefer gradual improvement to constant revolution. I also like WordPress&#8217;s regular every-4-months release schedule, which can be relied upon. Features can&#8217;t be added until they&#8217;re ready (there&#8217;s always next time, which isn&#8217;t far off).</p>\n\n<p>The most interesting change for UpdraftPlus in WP 4.2 is &#8220;shiny plugin updates&#8221;. Note that the WP Beginner article above is already out-of-date: support for &#8220;shiny plugin installs&#8221; has been dropped from the plan; it&#8217;s now only updates. What is this about? Basically, updating plugins currently looks like this:</p>\n\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-106296\" src=\"http://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/screenshot-12.png\" alt=\"Traditional plugin updates\" width=\"704\" height=\"232\" /></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>It&#8217;s a bit ugly. I&#8217;m a programmer: I like seeing the information; but even I can admit that it&#8217;s unnecessary. Information of this sort is good when something&#8217;s broken and needs fixing; otherwise, it&#8217;s noise and we don&#8217;t need to see it.</p>\n\n<p>&#8220;Shiny updates&#8221; means making this prettier. In future, on your plugins page (it&#8217;s only being implemented on that page in the first stage), you&#8217;ll see your update link, like so&#8230;</p>\n\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-106299\" src=\"http://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/screenshot-121.png\" alt=\"Update available\" width=\"700\" height=\"330\" /></p>\n\n<p>.. and when you click on the &#8220;update now&#8221; link (bottom, just right-of-centre), it&#8217;ll turn into &#8220;Updating&#8230;&#8221;:</p>\n\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-106302\" src=\"http://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/screenshot-122.png\" alt=\"Updating...\" width=\"700\" height=\"245\" /></p>\n\n<p>&#8230; and finally, if successful, it&#8217;ll tell you so:</p>\n\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-106303\" src=\"http://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/screenshot-123.png\" alt=\"Updated\" width=\"700\" height=\"245\" /></p>\n\n<p>Earth-shattering, this is not. But small improvements are nice too. Under-the-hood, it changes the way updates are done a lot, so this small tweak brought us a lot of work to get &#8220;Automatic Backups&#8221; working again. (&#8220;Automatic Backups&#8221; are our very handy, and unique, feature, whereby an appropriate is taken just before you do a plugin update &#8211; so that, if the new plugin is faulty, you can quickly switch back to the old one&#8230; without having to take special effort and risk not bothering and being caught out).</p>\n\n<p>The work is done now and is included in <a title=\"UpdraftPlus 1.9.62 / 2.9.62\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-1-9-62-2-9-62/\">the just-released UpdraftPlus 2.9.62</a>.</p>\n\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-106306 size-full\" src=\"http://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/screenshot-125.png\" alt=\"Automatic backups\" width=\"586\" height=\"342\" /></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/core/version-4-2-project-schedule/\">WordPress 4.2 is scheduled for release in 3 weeks from now</a>. If you&#8217;ve not got UpdraftPlus Premium with its &#8220;Automatic Backups&#8221; feature yet, then <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/shop/updraftplus-premium/\">please do take a look </a>- it&#8217;ll take a backup of your WordPress site for you before you update to 4.2, so that whatever 4.2 brings, you&#8217;ll be covered.</p>\n\n<p>David Anderson (founder, lead developer, UpdraftPlus)</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com/wordpress-4-2-shiny-updates/\">WordPress 4.2 &#8220;shiny updates&#8221;</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"http://updraftplus.com/wordpress-4-2-shiny-updates/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"http://updraftplus.com/wordpress-4-2-shiny-updates/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"UpdraftPlus 1.9.62 / 2.9.62\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/UpdraftPlus/~3/4fcgswID6Ok/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"http://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-1-9-62-2-9-62/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 01 Apr 2015 16:01:27 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"updates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"french\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"new release\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21:\"new wordpress release\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"translations\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"http://updraftplus.com/?p=105916\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:694:\"<p>UpdraftPlus 1.9.62 (or 2.9.62, for paid versions) is in process of being released. This is mostly a maintenance release with a number of slight improvements. The main feature is that it has been tested for compatibility with the forthcoming WordPress &#8230; <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-1-9-62-2-9-62/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-1-9-62-2-9-62/\">UpdraftPlus 1.9.62 / 2.9.62</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"udadmin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4629:\"<p>UpdraftPlus 1.9.62 (or 2.9.62, for paid versions) is in process of being released. This is mostly a maintenance release with a number of slight improvements.</p>\n\n<p>The main feature is that it has been tested for compatibility with the forthcoming WordPress 4.2 release. WordPress 4.2 changes the way in which plugin updates take place in your WordPress dashboard, and <a title=\"UpdraftPlus - premium WP backup, restore and clone\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/shop/updraftplus-premium/\">UpdraftPlus Premium&#8217;s</a> &#8220;automatic backup before update&#8221; feature has been adapted accordingly. (If you&#8217;ve not yet checked out <a title=\"UpdraftPlus - premium WP backup, restore and clone\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/shop/updraftplus-premium/\">UpdraftPlus Premium</a>, our flagship product, then please do have a look). Also, French users will be glad to see that Erwan François has stepped in and brought the French translation back up to parity with other included languages.</p>\n\n<p>You should see this release in your WordPress dashboard in the next day or two; it&#8217;s a recommended update for everyone.</p>\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s the full changelog:</p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li><strong>Feature:</strong> Automatic backups now integrate with the forthcoming WP 4.2&#8217;s &#8220;shiny plugin updates&#8221;</li>\n    <li><strong>Compatibility:</strong> Tested and marked compatible with the forthcoming WordPress 4.2 (tested up to beta 3)</li>\n    <li><strong>Fix:</strong> Fix regression in 1.9.60 for corner-case of S3 users with no permission to check their bucket&#8217;s location (but permission to write to it).</li>\n    <li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Make &#8220;settings saved&#8221; message disappear after a few seconds, to prevent UI clutter</li>\n    <li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Decrease UI clutter in backup time selection</li>\n    <li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Update to latest global SSL CA bundle, removing again 1024-bit root CAs (last attempted in 1.9.26, but S3 still had some legacy servers). Modern web browsers have not accepted these for 6 months now. (SSL verification can be turned off in the expert options).</li>\n    <li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Defeat WP Download Manager Google Drive plugin&#8217;s loading of its SDK on all pages (conflicting with UD when UD attempts to backup to Google Drive)</li>\n    <li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Detect case of old MySQL on Windows with table prefix that varies by case (and hence WP actually only works by accident) &#8211; produce a consistent backup that can be restored on any MySQL server.</li>\n    <li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Add dashboard notice with links to more resources, for free users who&#8217;ve been installed &gt;4 weeks (with option to dismiss notice)</li>\n    <li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Add itsec_log to the list of tables of non-essential/not-needing-search/replace + likely to be large tables for backup strategy</li>\n    <li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Improvement to scheduling algorithm in case where WP&#8217;s scheduler starts same resumption multiple times &#8211; prevent next attempt being delayed longer than necessary</li>\n    <li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Add a header to report emails indicating the job ID &#8211; helps when debugging</li>\n    <li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Detect + show a more helpful error message if blocked by CloudFlare when connecting for updates (paid versions)</li>\n    <li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Make it easier to use custom Dropbox API keys, via UPDRAFTPLUS_CUSTOM_DROPBOX_APP constant (define to true in wp-config.php)</li>\n    <li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Tweak debug output of webserver information to avoid triggering a (silly) mod_security rule in some setups</li>\n    <li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Alert the user if using Amazon S3 if they do not have the PHP XML Writer module available</li>\n    <li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Log the fact that local deletions are being skipped, if the user set that option.</li>\n    <li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Give timestamp of WPB2D backups without relying upon location of SQL file</li>\n    <li><strong>Translations:</strong> French translation updated from less than half to complete, thanks to Erwan François. Various other translations updated (many thanks to all translators).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>David Anderson (founder, lead developer, UpdraftPlus)</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-1-9-62-2-9-62/\">UpdraftPlus 1.9.62 / 2.9.62</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-1-9-62-2-9-62/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:49:\"http://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-1-9-62-2-9-62/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"UpdraftPlus on YouTube\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/UpdraftPlus/~3/4cRU6FvBVM8/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:55:\"http://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-on-youtube/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 01 Apr 2015 14:01:50 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Tips and tricks\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"http://updraftplus.com/?p=105902\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:717:\"<p>If you subscribe to our fortnightly newsletter then you&#8217;ll already know that we&#8217;ve recently launched a YouTube Channel. Over the coming months we&#8217;ll be creating tutorial videos covering various support queries, as well as sharing WordPress tips, resources and latest &#8230; <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-on-youtube/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-on-youtube/\">UpdraftPlus on YouTube</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Matt May\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:981:\"<p>If you subscribe to our <a href=\"http://try.updraftplus.com/newslettersignup/\" target=\"_blank\">fortnightly newsletter</a> then you&#8217;ll already know that we&#8217;ve recently launched a YouTube Channel. Over the coming months we&#8217;ll be creating tutorial videos covering various support queries, as well as sharing WordPress tips, resources and latest news.</p>\n\n<p>Although we are compatible with a wide-range of storage options &#8211; which we&#8217;ll cover over time &#8211; in our most recent video we look at how easy it is to backup to Dropbox. <a href=\"http://s87.eu/Upload\" target=\"_blank\">Take a look here</a> and for future updates, please subscribe!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-on-youtube/\">UpdraftPlus on YouTube</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"http://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-on-youtube/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"http://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-on-youtube/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s: